cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper deals with analyzing the phenomenon of fame and mining a collection of news articles and blog posts, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the appearance of Twitter and the Internet, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves analyzing data and tracking changes across decades, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming).
